8d92			; https://tutorials.eeems.ca/ASMin28Days/lesson/day16.html#cmp 
8d92			 
8d92			; String Length 
8d92			;With a length-prefixed string, finding the length is trivial. For a null-terminated string, the process is decidedly more involved. This is where CPIR comes in. 
8d92			 
8d92			; Get the length of the null-terminated string starting at $8000 hl 
8d92			;    LD     HL, $8000 
8d92			 
8d92			strlenz: 
8d92			 
8d92 af			    XOR    A               ; Zero is the value we are looking for. 
8d93 47			    LD     B, A             ; Since we haven't the slightest clue as to the  
8d94 4f			    LD     C, A             ; actual size of the string, put 0 in BC to search 
8d95			                           ; 65, 536 bytes (the entire addressable memory space). 
8d95 ed b1		    CPIR                   ; Begin search for a byte equalling zero. 
8d97			 
8d97			; BC has been decremented so that it holds -length. Now need to synthesize a NEG BC. 
8d97 67			    LD     H, A             ; Zero HL (basically set it to 65, 536) to get the 
8d98 6f			    LD     L, A             ; number of bytes 
8d99 ed 42		    SBC    HL, BC           ; Find the size. CPIR doesn't affect carry. 
8d9b 2b			    DEC    HL              ; Compensate for null. 
8d9c c9				ret 
8d9d			 
8d9d			; Get the length of the A terminated string starting at $8000 hl 
8d9d			;    LD     HL, $8000 
8d9d			 
8d9d			strlent: 
8d9d			 
8d9d			                  ; A is the value we are looking for. 
8d9d 06 00		    LD     B, 0             ; Since we haven't the slightest clue as to the  
8d9f 0e 00		    LD     C, 0             ; actual size of the string, put 0 in BC to search 
8da1			                           ; 65, 536 bytes (the entire addressable memory space). 
8da1 ed b1		    CPIR                   ; Begin search for a byte equalling zero. 
8da3			 
8da3			; BC has been decremented so that it holds -length. Now need to synthesize a NEG BC. 
8da3 26 00		    LD     H, 0             ; Zero HL (basically set it to 65, 536) to get the 
8da5 2e 00		    LD     L, 0             ; number of bytes 
8da7 ed 42		    SBC    HL, BC           ; Find the size. CPIR doesn't affect carry. 
8da9 2b			    DEC    HL              ; Compensate for null. 
8daa c9				ret 
